<subSubSection box="[151,761,1770,1797]" pageId="1" pageNumber="137" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,761,1770,1797]" box="[151,761,1770,1797]" pageId="1" pageNumber="137">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,761,1770,1797]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="1" pageNumber="137" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,761,1770,1797]" pageId="1" pageNumber="137">
Tribe 
<taxonomicName authority="Brunner von Wattenwyl, 1888" authorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" authorityYear="1888" box="[226,761,1770,1797]" class="Insecta" family="Anostostomatidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Cratomelini">
Cratomelini 
<bibRefCitation author="Brunner von Wattenwyl, C." box="[385,761,1770,1797]" pageId="1" pageNumber="137" pagination="247 - 394" refId="ref4900" refString="Brunner von Wattenwyl, C. (1888) Monographie der Stenopelmatiden und Gryllacriden. Verhandlungen der Zoologisch- Botanischen Gesellschaft Wien, 38, 247 - 394." type="journal article" year="1888">Brunner von Wattenwyl, 1888</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="138" pageId="1" pageNumber="137" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1842,2013]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1436,151,285]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="138" pageId="1" pageNumber="137">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,287,1842,1868]" pageId="1" pageNumber="137">Comments.</emphasis>
This tribe was originally described as Cratomeli by 
<bibRefCitation author="Brunner von Wattenwyl, C." box="[873,1226,1843,1869]" pageId="1" pageNumber="137" pagination="247 - 394" refId="ref4900" refString="Brunner von Wattenwyl, C. (1888) Monographie der Stenopelmatiden und Gryllacriden. Verhandlungen der Zoologisch- Botanischen Gesellschaft Wien, 38, 247 - 394." type="journal article" year="1888">Brunner von Wattenwyl (1888)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Gorochov, A. V." box="[1236,1431,1843,1869]" pageId="1" pageNumber="137" pagination="353 - 366" refId="ref5450" refString="Gorochov, A. V. (1988) System and phylogeny of the recent Orthoptera of the superfamilies Hagloidea and Stenopelmatoidea with a description of new taxa. Communication 1. Zoologicheskii Zhurnal, 67 (3), 353 - 366." type="journal article" year="1988">Gorochov (1988)</bibRefCitation>
, raised it to the family rank (Cratomelidae), including as subfamilies Cratomelinae and Anabropsinae (
<bibRefCitation author="Gorochov, A. V." pageId="1" pageNumber="137" pagination="353 - 366" refId="ref5450" refString="Gorochov, A. V. (1988) System and phylogeny of the recent Orthoptera of the superfamilies Hagloidea and Stenopelmatoidea with a description of new taxa. Communication 1. Zoologicheskii Zhurnal, 67 (3), 353 - 366." type="journal article" year="1988">Gorochov 1988</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Gorochov, A. V." box="[227,287,1914,1941]" pageId="1" pageNumber="137" pagination="1 - 224" refId="ref5494" refString="Gorochov, A. V. (1995) System and evolution of the suborder Ensifera (Orthoptera). Part I [in Russian]. Proceedings of the Zoological Institute of the Russian Academy of Sciences, 260, 1 - 224." type="journal article" year="1995">1995</bibRefCitation>
). Sometime later, 
<bibRefCitation author="Johns, P. M." box="[508,659,1915,1941]" pageId="1" pageNumber="137" pagination="125 - 138" refId="ref5790" refString="Johns, P. M. (1997) The Gondwanaland Weta FamilyAnostostomatidae (formerly in Stenopelmatidae, Henicidae or Mimnermidae): nomenclatural problems, world checklist, new genera and species. Journal of Orthoptera Research, 6, 125 - 138. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 3503546" type="journal article" year="1997">Johns (1997)</bibRefCitation>
established the family 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Saussure" authorityYear="1859" box="[941,1143,1915,1941]" class="Insecta" family="Anostostomatidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Anostostomatidae</taxonomicName>
and proposed the status of a tribe to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" authorityYear="1888" box="[301,438,1951,1977]" class="Insecta" family="Anostostomatidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Cratomelini">Cratomelini</taxonomicName>
, including only 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Blanchard" authorityYear="1851" box="[629,760,1951,1977]" class="Insecta" family="Anostostomatidae" genus="Cratomelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[629,760,1951,1977]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="137">Cratomelus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Gorochov, A. V." box="[777,976,1951,1977]" pageId="1" pageNumber="137" pagination="3 - 33" refId="ref5573" refString="Gorochov, A. V. (2001) The higher classification, phylogeny and evolution of the superfamily Stenopelmatoidea. In: Field, L. H. (Ed.), The Biology of Wetas, King Crickets and their Allies, pp. 3 - 33. https: // doi. org / 10.1079 / 9780851994086.0003" type="book chapter" year="2001">Gorochov (2001)</bibRefCitation>
, in his classification of the superfamily 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Burmeister" authorityYear="1838" box="[151,355,1987,2013]" class="Magnoliopsida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="1" pageNumber="137" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="superFamily" superFamily="Stenopelmatoidea">Stenopelmatoidea</taxonomicName>
, raised the rank to subfamily as Cratomelinae, and the same author rectifies his classification and returns this taxon to tribal status (
<bibRefCitation author="Gorochov, A. V." box="[589,773,151,177]" pageId="2" pageNumber="138" pagination="1106 - 1151" refId="ref5634" refString="Gorochov, A. V. (2020) The families Stenopelmatidae and Anostostomatidae (Orthoptera). 1. Higher classification, new and little known taxa. Entomological Review, 100 (8), 1106 - 1151. https: // doi. org / 10.1134 / S 0013873820080084" type="journal article" year="2020">Gorochov 2020</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" authorityYear="1888" box="[794,931,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Anostostomatidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Cratomelini">Cratomelini</taxonomicName>
, like the other suprageneric taxa of chevron crickets, usually start as a genus or tribe, passing as a subfamily and, in some cases reaching family status, due to differences in the perspective of the taxonomic status of the authors (
<bibRefCitation author="Cadena-Castaneda, O. J. &amp; Cortes-Torres, C." box="[957,1432,223,249]" pageId="2" pageNumber="138" pagination="335 - 348" refId="ref4976" refString="Cadena-Castaneda, O. J. &amp; Cortes-Torres, C. (2013) New species and taxonomic rearrangements of Anostostomatid Crickets (Orthoptera: Stenopelmatoidea: Anostostomatidae) from the Neotropics. Zootaxa, 3664 (3), 335 - 348. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3664.3.4" type="journal article" year="2013">Cadena-Castañeda &amp; Cortés-Torres 2013</bibRefCitation>
, Cadena-Castañeda &amp; Weissman 2020, 
<bibRefCitation author="Gorochov, A. V. &amp; Cadena-Castaneda, O. J." box="[586,1008,259,285]" pageId="2" pageNumber="138" pagination="1" refId="ref5686" refString="Gorochov, A. V. &amp; Cadena-Castaneda, O. J. (2016) New and little known Stenopelmatoidea (Orthoptera: Ensifera) from America. Zoosystematica Rossica, 25 (1), 98 - 14. https: // doi. org / 10.31610 / zsr / 2016.25.1.98" type="journal article" year="2016">Gorochov &amp; Cadena-Castañeda 2016</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Johns, P. M. &amp; Hemp, C." box="[1019,1255,258,285]" pageId="2" pageNumber="138" pagination="113 - 124" refId="ref5845" refString="Johns, P. M. &amp; Hemp, C. (2015) Redescription of Libanasa brachyura Karny, 1928 (Orthoptera: Anostostomatidae:? Lutosinae) from Tanzania and problems at the subfamily level. Zootaxa, 3946 (1), 113 - 124. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3946.1.5" type="journal article" year="2015">Johns &amp; Hemp 2015</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
